The paper deals with a problem of computing sums over subsets of a ground set, which is a classic topic in discrete mathematics and algorithms. The use of arithmetic circuits and monotone gates suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). The applications to graph algorithms and machine learning suggest connections to combinatorics (cs.DM), machine learning (cs.LG), and computational geometry (cs.CG).
